<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The loading of data should be taken out of the constructor of the config classes and move to a seperate load method.</p>

<p>This would allow for just in time loading of data.</p>

<p>The load method should only be called for any the data access operations (only loading once).</p>

<p>It will mean a minor refactor with no change to the signatures of the methods so it should not effect any users.</p>

