        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Darby Felton (darby) on 2007-02-28T14:56:02.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>Though in principle I agree that it would be optimal to only load configuration data on-demand, it is unlikely that applications will benefit to more than a negligible amount from this particular change. This is due in part to the nature of the data Zend_Config presents to the application, but more so because of the cost of loading the configuration file relative to the rest of the application. This is likely to be a case of premature optimization.</p>

<p>In the interest of expediting resolution of this issue, I have marked it "not an issue" until it is demonstrated (hopefully with code) that a common and appropriate use case would benefit significantly from such a change.</p>

